title: For Sale:  AR 15-5.56/.223 -Not Cheap, 1 of a Kind
postcontent: This isn't an inexpensive rifle-there are plenty on the market now, so if money is your primary concern, don't look any further. Why is this one of a kind? It was not built to sell or for a showpiece.People often refer to their gun as "rare" to get your attention or justify a high price. This rifle starts with a Palmetto receiver sn SC000XXX. If you're familiar with Palmetto you recognize that's not a normal SN. The SC denoted South Carolina and the manufacturer of the receiver-FN.This is one of 500 made by FN for Palmetto while FN was only building for the military, and prior to them entering the commercial market.The barrel is a Black Hole Weaponry 16 inch 1-8 twist polygonal barrel, mid length, stainless steel, pencil configuration. Polygonal barrels are noted as the most accurate, durable, and easily cleaned type.
